			<text id="header" x="225" y="15" width="278" height="" autosize="H" style="PANEL_HEADER" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">Language Skills of Children Ages 3–5</content>
			</text>
			<text id="text" x="225" y="40" width="342" height="" autosize="H" style="PANEL" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Language skills develop quickly and significantly in children ages 3 to 5 years. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Some research indicates that preschoolers learn approximately nine new words a day. Children's ability to use and combine these words to express themselves also increases during the preschool years. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;By age 5, most children have learned approximately 5,000 words. &lt;/P&gt;</content>
			</text>
